main event: Two air traffic controllers at Grand Ledge Airport in Michigan observed an unidentified flying object on radar on February 13, 1964.
interesting points: The object appeared on radar and was tracked for 75 seconds.
The object was described as stationary and not moving.
The controllers believed the radar return was caused by a reflection of car headlights on a patch of fog, rather than a physical object.
No photographs were taken of the object.
The report indicates that the Air Force received numerous calls reporting similar sightings in the area, but they were all determined to have natural explanations.
